You do not need the extra else branch for param.ord. Just do:
```c++
If (param.ord == 2) {
     // original storage type assign logic
}
if (!dispatched) {
      dispatched = dispatch_fallback(out_attrs, dispatch_mode);
}
```

Write this as:

    list.push({
        revision: revisionSet.revision,
        author: revisionSet.author
    })

minor style issue, but this might be better written like:

```javascript
const transforms = ['translate(-50%, -50%)'];
if (this.isRtl) {
  // must mirror first, order matters
  transforms.unshift('scaleX(-1)');
}
return { transform: transforms.join(' ') };
```

doing string concatenation with `+` is brittle because of the spaces.

Would we be able to clean this up using some more of [_.forEach](https://lodash.com/docs#forEach)'s functionality? Or does marionette not like that?

'_.forEach({ 'a': 1, 'b': 2 }, function(value, key) {
  console.log(key);
});'

Looks good to me, but following form can save memory allocation as well reduce indention.

``` python
if snapshot and sas_token:
    url = '{}?snapshot={}&{}'.format(url, snapshot, sas)
elif snapshot:
    url = '{}?snapshot={}'.format(url, snapshot)
elif sas_token:
    url = '{}?{}'.format(url, sas)

